<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900730-0054</DOCNO><DOCID>900730-0054.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Arix Corp.:   Minicomputer Firm Expects   To Report 4th-Quarter Loss</HL><DATE>07/30/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   ARIX</CO><LP>   Arix Corp. said it expects to report a loss of $20 millionto $22 million for its fourth quarter, ended June 30, becauseof charges related to shrinking its main unit.   The San Jose, Calif., minicomputer maker also said itsdeteriorating condition will reduce its ability to borrowunder its existing bank line of credit to about $2.9 million.It said it is seeking alternate financing sources but didn'telaborate.</LP><TEXT>   Arix has been hurt by declining revenue from its biggestcustomer, Unisys Corp.   It said the charges, which will total $12 million to $14million, relate to employee-termination costs, to costs ofterminating leases and to write-downs.   Arix also said it expects to report that fourth-quarterrevenue plunged 65% to $7 million from $20 million. For thefirst nine months, the company had a net loss of $11.2million, or $1.46 a share, on revenue of $49.6 million.   In over-the-counter trading Friday, Arix closed at$1.9375, down 6.25 cents.</TEXT></DOC>